snippet.textDisplay: I do feel that this video is a misrepresentation of what's happening here, or at least what's being communicated to us here. It now seems as though 'herd immunity' is proposed as a short term solution, but we are doing the same thing countries around us are doing: try to control the spread to the extent that the healthcare system can cope. We try that by keeping people inside, minimising social contacts (groups larger than 3 people will be fined, parks and beaches are being monitored) and using proper hygiene. The idea of herd immunity is basically presented to us as an alternative to a complete lockdown. A complete lockdown meaning going out with written permission, one family member per household can go out, and other strict regulations like the ones being experimented with throughout the world. In the long term a complete lockdown might have to be prolonged again and again and people will keep getting sick with every uprise of the virus. I mean, this virus won't be gone in a couple of months. So with every uprise of the virus countries will have to go into lockdown again, and herd immunity might free us from having to keep imposing strict regulations a while from now. I mean, this is my interpretation and I'm not a scientist, so if I'm wrong, I'm wrong. But I hope it might be a pragmatic long term approach to this pandemic.

snippet.textDisplay: Everyone is acting like the Netherlands is crazy, but what choice do they (or any of the rest of us) have? We aren't going to quarantine this virus away. Its transmission rate is way too high and this global pandemic began with just a few people in China becoming infected. Here in the US effectively "flattening the curve" would mean living in quarantine for years. So... What's our end game here?! The quarantine isn't sustainable enough for us to do for long enough for it to be of any use. And as soon as we stop the quarantine, the spike everyone seems to think is flattening will happen. In a quite non-flat way, I might add. The only thing that will stop the virus is herd immunity, whether that immunity comes from people getting infected and recovering, or a vaccine which is still 18 months out. To get that immunity, we can play the long game (slow the new infection rate with quarantine and live like this for years) or the short game (just let the virus do its thing and be back to normal in a couple months). In the meantime, with all businesses shut down, COVID19 is bankrupting more people and ruining more lives than it could ever kill.

snippet.textDisplay:
For those who are not living in the Netherlands: we have a quasi-lockdown. Almost all non-essential stores (including restaurants, pubs, international brands, local shops) are closed, all lot of essential stores (including take away)have strict regulation , public transport is at a minimum ( example: 1 or 2 trains per hour), non-essential travels by flight and across border by car are prohibited, schools are closed, the vulnerable people are in a lockdown and will be protected by the government, a lot of people belonging to the Dutch workforce work at home, social interaction with more than 3 people is prohibited, some public places are closed by the orders of the city councils, beaches and some nature reservations are closed, the whole Dutch community is advised to stay home as much as possible.

The Premier Minister stated that their way to handle the situation is not necessarily best option, but a lockdown can be as much a risk as the Dutch system. However, we don't want a total lockdown (yet), because it will effect economic and social life not only now, but for the years to come. We don't want to wait for a vaccine, that presumably will be in the hands of a few American companies. We are trying to outlive this crisis by slowly moving forward, instead of being at the same place because of the lockdown.

snippet.textDisplay:
This is a very wrong title, please do some research. I sent the mail below to Vice, asking for rectification.


I am writing you because of the following video Vice News uploaded on Youtube:
"The Netherlands Is Letting People Get Sick to Beat Coronavirus"
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ozmh40wwAGc

First of all I want to state that I have no affiliation with the Dutch government or any political party/movement whatsoever.

The reason I took the time to write this mail is the blatant incorrectness of the mentioned video's title. The Dutch government does not aim to achieve herd immunity, let alone count on herd immunity for the battle against the corona virus.

The incredible misunderstanding of such difficult matter is visible everywhere on the internet. Because I usually enjoy Vice's content, my disappointment in this work is even worse. I suggest you publicly rectify your mistake and try harder to avoid such journalistic laziness in the future.

Some references that should have been used before:
https://www.tweedekamer.nl/sites/default/files/atoms/files/20200325_briefing_coronavirus_tweede_kamer_presentatie_rivm.pdf
https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/onderwerpen/coronavirus-covid-19/nieuws/2020/03/24/aanvullende-maatregelen-23-maart

snippet.textDisplay: I'd like everyone to imagine "Corona Virus Healed" headline. What would that feel like? Picture you pick up your phone one morning ,while drinking your coffee and you see THOSE HEADLINES, "Corona Virus STABILIZED Thank God!" What would your reaction be? Right now let that emotion fill up your entire being.......I walked 60 people, while standing in line, through a visualization that manifested our bus that previously got canceled. We had to sleep at the bus station on benches and the floor, while it was 3 feet of snow and -22F outside. We weren't the only group waiting for their bus. Bottom line, our bus was the only bus that showed up that day. Simple atoms are our building blocks and to be stable they need a balance of negative and positive energy just like we do. Therefore, it is important each one of us be the light in the dark; express positive emotion to negative; it is a healthy balance and it will bring stability....
